The paper discusses machine learning and signal processing tasks, which are typically covered in the computer science sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The focus on developing efficient pursuit algorithms for parsimonious modeling suggests a potential fit with cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
